  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Use</h2>

  <p>
    Use rigid, purpose-built trellis connectors if you want a cucumber teepee that stays stable through the full season. They reduce shifting, improve structure, and handle real plant weight better than simple ties.
  </p>

  <p>
    DIY methods can work early, but they rarely hold up under full growth.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Build for the weight you’ll have — not the structure you see on day one.
  </p>
